Root User :
• The superuser in Linux with full administrative privileges.
• Can access, modify, or delete any file or system setting.
• Used for system administration tasks.

UID range:0

System Users :
• Created automatically for system services and daemons.
• Do not log in interactively.
• Used by services like web servers, databases, and background processes.

Examples: www-data, mysql, daemon
UID range: 1–999

Normal Users
• Regular users created for human login.
• Have limited permissions.
• Cannot perform administrative tasks without sudo.

UID range: 1000 and above
